      "bodyHtml": "<div class=\"group\" id=\"q1-2-3-4-5-6-anchor\"><h4>Questions 1-6</h4><p>Complete the notes below.</p><p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>\n<div class=\"notes-completion\"><h5>The early history of graphite in Britain</h5>\n<ul><li>Graphite was first found below a <strong>1</strong> <input class=\"blank\" name=\"q1\" type=\"text\"> blown down in a storm.</li><li>The first use of graphite was to make marks on <strong>2</strong> <input class=\"blank\" name=\"q2\" type=\"text\">.</li><li>The characteristics of raw graphite: dirty to use because it is so <strong>3</strong> <input class=\"blank\" name=\"q3\" type=\"text\">; originally wrapped in <strong>4</strong> <input class=\"blank\" name=\"q4\" type=\"text\"> or animal skin to make it useable as a pencil.</li><li>The government completely took over the <strong>5</strong> <input class=\"blank\" name=\"q5\" type=\"text\"> at Borrowdale.</li><li>Local people began to <strong>6</strong> <input class=\"blank\" name=\"q6\" type=\"text\"> graphite for the money involved.</li></ul></div></div>",
